3 Then is my strength by thee renewed ;
Then are my sins by thee forgiven ;
Then dost thou cheer my solitude
4 No words can tell what sweet relief

4 No words can tell what sweet relief There for my every want I find ; What strength for warfare , balm for grief , What peace of mind !

1 I can not always trace the way Where thou , almighty One , dost move ; But I can always , always say , That God is love .

2 When fear her chilling mantle flings O'er earth , my soul to heaven above , As to her native home , upsprings ; For God is love .

4 Oh may this truth my heart employ , And every gloomy thought remove ; It fills my soul with boundless joy , That God is love !
